Name: Corn
Description: Corn appears to have a yellowish-purple color, suggesting it may be related to flint maize, also known as Indian corn.

Name: Tato
Description: The outside looks like a tomato, but the inside is brown. Tastes absolutely disgusting as it looks, but the starch will keep you from starving.

Name: .45 Ammo
Description: The .45 Auto is an effective pistol cartridge for use against soft, unarmored targets.

Name: .308 Ammo
Description: A box of high-powered .308 rounds, found in a large number of locations.

Name: Submachine Gun
Description: A Tommy Gun. Voted: Pre-War American Gangster’s Weapon of Choice. Capable of firing 800 45 ACPs a minute in top condition.

Name: Hunting Rifle
Description: A Modified Colt Rangemaster rechambered to hold .308s. Effective at most ranges above ten feet, but best at medium to long range due to a single-fire restriction.

Name: Nuka Cola
Description: An old Glass Bottle with dark liquid sloshing around inside, plainly labeled ‘Nuka-Cola’. You’d think it couldn’t be this sweet after a couple centuries.

Name: Army Helmet
Description: A sturdy helmet worn by military personnel.

Name: Military Fatigues
Description: Fatigues worn by military personnel.

Name: Stimpak
Description: The Stimpak is a type of hand-held medication used for healing the body.

Name: Shirt and Combat Boots
Description: Green shirt and rugged combat boots.

Name: Small Cap Stash
Description: Cap Stash, can be traded in for 300 caps at any shop.

Name: Blood Bag
Description: The bloodpack is an IV bag full of blood.

Name: Dirty Water
Description: A carton of lake water, contaminated by radioactive fallout.

Name: Purified Water
Description: Before the Great War, the Lake Tahoe Bottling Co. purified and bottled this water, intended to be used in an emergency.

Name: Cram
Description: Cram is processed meat from before the War, found in blue cardboard boxes.

Name: Gumdrops
Description: A Prewar sweet, some wasteland junkies lace the candy with chems to avoid confiscation in NCR Territory.

Name: Gumdrops
Description: A Prewar sweet, the packaging has obviously been tampered with.

Name: Instamash
Description: Box full of the necessary ingredients to make stale instant mashed potatoes.

Name: Sugar Bombs
Description: A Prewar breakfast cereal, the cereal pieces are modeled off mini nukes and sport "Explosive Great Taste!".

Name: Deviled Eggs
Description: Freeze dried "eggs" produced by the prewar Yum Yum food company. The presence of actual egg is doubtful.

Name: Potato Chips
Description: Salty, Dry and Crumbled, these Prewar potato chips will do in a pinch..

Name: Dog Food
Description: A large rusty tin of Beef stew Dog Food.

Name: Fancy Lads Snacks
Description: Prewar biscuits covered in powdered sugar. A robust marketing campaign preserved this snack's reputation even after the Great War.

Name: Pork n Beans
Description: Salty chunks of pig fat and beans have fed generations of the American cowboy, and still does 200 years later.

Name: Can of Sardines
Description: Can of oily sardines, the container is sealed and the fish is safe to eat.

Name: Salisbury Steak
Description: Freeze dried slabs of meat with foil gravy packets.

Name: Dandy Boy Apples
Description: Box full of artifical apples shock full of preservatives.

Name: Blamco MacCheese
Description: Wheat cannot be freeze dried, how this stuff is still edible makes you question the ingredients list.

Name: Vegetable Soup
Description: Nutritious vegetable broth produced by many of the small towns in the wasteland.

Description: A ragged wasteland jacket and tie.

Description: Stained Kahki jumpsuit, with metal wire wrapped around one arm.

Name: Vault Suit
Description: An old dusty Vault suit. Probably pilfered from a Vault Tec shipping crate.

Name: Rags
Description: Dirty torn rags. Pretty depressing, even for a Wastelander.

Description: A coat inlaid with ballistic kevlar and lead plates.

Name: Greaser Jacket
Description: Leather jacket worn over a t-shirt, faded jeans and worn sneakers.

Description: A popular pre-War detergent produced by Abraxodyne Chemical.

Description: A rubber suction cup attached to a wooden handle.

Name: Small Pan

Name: Prewar Money

Name: Silver Brush
Description: A silver hairbrush with white plastic bristles and a floral pattern on the back.

Name: Rat Poison

Description: Hinged pieces of jewellery, typically used to hold a small keepsake or photograph.

Name: Spatula
Description: A flat steel cooking utensil with a rubber handle.

Description: A small, copper colored tea pot.

Name: Tea Cup Saucer
Description: A small ceramic plate

Name: Toothpaste
Description: A valuable commodity, most Wastelanders eat it for the taste.

Name: Yarn
Description: A small spool of colored yarn.

Name: Cigarette Pack
Description: A pack of smokes never really goes out of fashion.

Name: Cigarette Carton
Description: A large box of cigarettes.

Name: Preserved Pie
Description: I don't trust anything that looks that perfectly preserved after 200 years.

Name: Duct Tape

Name: Rotten Food
Description: A disgusting plate of rotten food.

Name: Gunslinger Hat

Name: Combat Helmet
Description: Reinforced military grade combat armor, excellent bullet, energy and blunt resistance.

Description: Enclave uniform worn by enclave officers.

Description: It's a sack with eyeholes. The material appears to be burlap or canvas.

Name: Sack Hood Tubes
Description: It's a sack with eyeholes. The material appears to be burlap or canvas.

Description: Cap worn by Enclave officers. Emblazoned with the Enclave sigil.
